A CHINESE restaurant - voted as the country's most popular - is to open in Glasgow. Chop Chop for city A CHINESE restaurant - voted as the country's most popular - is to open in Glasgow.Chop Chop, which has been awarded two AA rosettes, will open in the city's Mitchell Street next month.The eatery has been a favourite in Edinburgh for eight years.It specialises in north eastern-style Chinese food.The Glasgow restaurant is set to become the flagship for the brand's chain expansion across the UK, with plans to open additional restaurants in Aberdeen and across England, following the same design.In an online poll, Chop Chop was voted Britain's most popular Chinese restaurant.The restaurant also landed a finalist spot on Gordon Ramsay's The F Word. 